cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automatic neuron reconstruction from electron microscopy data, which is a common application of computer vision techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper presents a structured learning framework for assignment models to minimize the TED on annotated training samples. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a measure to compare the labeling of automatic neuron reconstruction methods against ground truth. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neuron reconstruction, which is related to the study of neural networks. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with visual data (electron microscopy images) and presents a method to localize errors in the volume.
